OL,6,FOne of the books for sale has no signs
OL,7,Fof it being read, except for a small
OL,8,Fmark on page 128. Jim Spencer, from
OL,9,Fthe Rare Books Auctions team, said
OL,10,Fhe's discovered 20 of the 500 books so
OL,11,Ffar- but the one that sold for #64,000
OL,12,Fis is one of the best conditions he
OL,13,Fhas ever seen.
OL,15,FThe other book is owned by Adam
OL,16,FMcCulloch from Chesterfield. His mum
OL,17,Fbought him the book thirty years ago
OL,18,Fin a charity shop. It was then put in
OL,19,Fa cupboard under the stairs, much like
OL,20,Fa young Harry himself!
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/9
